message.content:
cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SOC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the analysis of a multiplex network of media attention and public attention.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper involves collecting and analyzing longitudinal data from online news and web search volume data.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper investigates the alignment of international attention of news media organizations with the expressed international interests of the public within those same countries.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper uses Granger causality to analyze the relationship between media attention and public attention.
- cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper examines the structural and dynamic properties of the multiplex network of media attention and public attention.
